Crud Repo
Repo will be a interface and extends with CrudRepository<EntityClassname,datatype(int)>
By deafult it has save findby, delete methods, no need to create it 


Most imp steps to include
1. add validation Annotation to the entity field.
@Size(Min=2, Max=3)
@NotBlank(message="username is required")----> when user not ggiving name and try to submit that time it wont allow and show the msg.

2. Implement @valid and Binding result(I) to the method wgich is handling request.(For validating the errors and binding result store the error)

3. Bind the Entity object and field in the HTML page
<form action="@{/register}"  th:object="${user}" method="post">

<input type="text" th:field="*{uname}" placeholder="Enter ur name"><br>
<input type="text" th:field="*{email}" placeholder="Enter ur email"><br>
<input type="password" th:field="*{pwd}" placeholder="enter the pwd"><br>

4. Add error HTML tag with Thymleaf condition
<p th:if="${#fields.hasErrors('uname')}" th:errors=*{uname}></p>
